about.summary: Provides iconv for systems which don't have one (or that cannot convert from/to Unicode.)

name: libiconv
raw_recipe:
{% set version = "1.14" %}

package:
  name: libiconv
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: libiconv-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: http://ftp.gnu.org/pub/gnu/libiconv/libiconv-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 72b24ded17d687193c3366d0ebe7cde1e6b18f0df8c55438ac95be39e8a30613
  patches:
    - glibc.patch  # [linux]
    - CMakeLists.txt.patch  # [win]
    - config.h.patch  # [win]
    - configure.cmake.patch  # [win]

build:
  number: 4
  features:
    - vc9  # [win and py27]
    - vc10  # [win and py34]
    - vc14  # [win and py35]

requirements:
  build:
    - python  # [win]
    - cmake  # [win]
    - vc 9  # [win and py27]
    - vc 10  # [win and py34]
    - vc 14  # [win and py35]
  run:
    - vc 9  # [win and py27]
    - vc 10  # [win and py34]
    - vc 14  # [win and py35]

test:
  commands:
    - iconv --help  # [not win]
    - conda inspect linkages -p $PREFIX libiconv  # [not win]
    - conda inspect objects -p $PREFIX libiconv  # [osx]

about:
  home: https://www.gnu.org/software/libiconv/
  license: GPL and LGPL
  summary: "Provides iconv for systems which don't have one (or that cannot convert from/to Unicode.)"

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
    - jakirkham
    - jhamman
